# ZERODRIFT — WordPress Migration

Source site IS destination site. Every table. Every file. Every version.

---

## WP-M1 — Plugin versions exact

```bash
# Extract from source
wp plugin list --format=csv --fields=name,version > plugins-source.csv

# Install exact versions on destination
while IFS=, read name version; do
  wp plugin install "$name" --version="$version" --activate
done < plugins-source.csv
```

Do not update during migration. Migration ≠ upgrade.

---

## WP-M2 — Core version exact

```bash
wp core download --version=6.4.3  # exact version from source
# NEVER: wp core download          # installs latest = drift
```

---

## WP-M3 — Database: full clone + FK validation

```bash
# Export ALL tables
wp db export source-full.sql --add-drop-table

# Import
wp db import source-full.sql

# URL replace — precise, all tables
wp search-replace 'https://source.com' 'https://dest.com' \
  --all-tables --precise --report-changed-only
```

Post-import FK integrity check (F-03):
```sql
-- Orphan post_authors (must return 0 rows)
SELECT ID, post_author FROM wp_posts
WHERE post_author NOT IN (SELECT ID FROM wp_users)
AND post_author != 0;

-- Orphan postmeta (must return 0 rows)
SELECT meta_id, post_id FROM wp_postmeta
WHERE post_id NOT IN (SELECT ID FROM wp_posts);

-- Orphan term_relationships (must return 0 rows)
SELECT tr.object_id, tr.term_taxonomy_id
FROM wp_term_relationships tr
LEFT JOIN wp_term_taxonomy tt ON tr.term_taxonomy_id = tt.term_taxonomy_id
WHERE tt.term_taxonomy_id IS NULL;
```

Run `references/wp-cli-verify.sh source-domain.com` for automated check.

