## WP-M4 — Media: rsync --delete, counts verified

```bash
rsync -avz --delete source:/wp-content/uploads/ dest:/wp-content/uploads/

# Verify
ssh source "find wp-content/uploads -type f | wc -l"
ssh dest   "find wp-content/uploads -type f | wc -l"
# Numbers must match exactly
```

---

## WP-M5 — wp-config.php: diff constant names

```bash
# Extract constant names from both configs
grep "define(" source-wp-config.php | grep -o "'[A-Z_]*'" | sort > constants-source.txt
grep "define(" dest-wp-config.php   | grep -o "'[A-Z_]*'" | sort > constants-dest.txt
diff constants-source.txt constants-dest.txt
# Must show: no differences in constant names
```

---

## WP-M6 — Theme: rsync --delete, no rewrites

```bash
rsync -avz --delete source:/wp-content/themes/client/ dest:/wp-content/themes/client/
# Theme migrates AS IS. No improvements during migration.
```

---

## WP-M7 — Settings verified post-migration

Verify manually:
- Site Title, Tagline, Timezone, Date Format
- Front page assignment, posts per page
- Permalink structure (identical string)
- All menus: names, items, order, assigned locations
- All widgets: areas, settings, order

---

## WP-M8 — Users and roles intact

```bash
wp user list --format=csv --fields=ID,user_login,roles > users-source.csv
# On destination:
wp user list --format=csv --fields=ID,user_login,roles > users-dest.csv
diff users-source.csv users-dest.csv  # Zero differences
```

