## ROLLBACK PROTOCOL (F-04)

Before migration begins:
```bash
# Tag the rollback point
wp db export "backup-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)-pre-migration.sql"
# Retain for minimum 30 days after go-live
```

Rollback triggers (conditions requiring rollback):
- Data loss detected (post count mismatch > 0)
- FK integrity failures not resolvable within 2 hours
- Critical functionality broken (checkout, login, forms)
- Client approval withdrawn

Rollback steps (reverse order):
```bash
# 1. Put destination in maintenance mode
wp maintenance-mode activate

# 2. Restore database from pre-migration backup
wp db import backup-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS-pre-migration.sql

# 3. Restore files if changed
rsync -avz --delete backup/wp-content/ /wp-content/

# 4. Restore wp-config.php
cp backup/wp-config.php ./wp-config.php

# 5. Flush and verify
wp cache flush && wp cron event run --due-now

# 6. Verify site loads on source domain
# 7. Document: what failed, what was rolled back, timestamp
```

---

## Exception Protocol

| Situation | Action |
|---|---|
| Plugin version unavailable in WP.org | STOP → find archived version → ask client |
| Source DB partially corrupted | STOP → restore from backup → document scope |
| Media file missing on source | STOP → generate missing-files.txt → ask client |
| Conflicting search-replace results | STOP → show diff → await decision |

Never improvise. Always escalate.
